edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.algorithms

Class TreeGrepMatch<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.illinois.cs.cogcomp.core.algorithms.TreeGrepMatch<T>

  • public class TreeGrepMatch<T>
extends Object
    This class holds the result of a single match for TreeGrep. For every pattern node, it can be used to recover the matching node in the tree that is being searched.

    Usage: Suppose match is an instance of TreeGrepMatch<T> that is generated by searching through a tree t for some pattern p.

    Then, the match object provides three methods to access the matching elements between the tree and the pattern.

    • getPatternDFSMatches(): This gives a list of matches for the nodes of the pattern, assuming that the pattern is traversed in depth first order. Use TreeTraversal.depthFirstTraversal(Tree) for depth first traversal of the pattern.
    • getPatternLeafMatches(): This gives a list of matches for just the leaves of the pattern.
    • getRootMatch(): This gets the node in the tree that matches the root of the pattern.

    Author:
    Vivek Srikumar
    See Also:
    TreeGrep, TreeTraversal.depthFirstTraversal(Tree)
